  "ComponentType": "Serial EEPROM (Electrically Erasable Programmable Read-Only Memory)",
  "Description": "The AT24C32 and AT24C64 are low-power, low-voltage serial EEPROM memory chips providing 32,768 bits (4 KB) and 65,536 bits (8 KB) of non-volatile storage, respectively. They are organized as 4096 x 8 or 8192 x 8 and are accessed via a two-wire I²C-compatible serial interface. Key features include hardware write protection via a dedicated pin, a 32-byte page write mode, and high reliability with 1 million write cycle endurance and 100-year data retention. They operate over a wide voltage range and are designed for industrial and commercial applications.",
